trend_summary: Imagery shows steady suburban consolidation. The northern highway corridor gains big-box retail, wider roads and warehouses, while interior woodlots see scattered residential infill. Tree canopy declines slightly; south-side wetlands stay protected and get park upgrades. No high-rise growth: settlement intensifies yet remains mostly single-family, keeping a medium-density suburban character.
notable_changes: Commercial roofs and parking lots proliferate along the northern highway interchange between earliest and latest frames.
A new big-box retail cluster appears east of the rail/road corridor, replacing forested land.
Scattered residential infill within central tree-lined streets reduces overall canopy cover.
Main arterial road is widened and re-aligned, generating a larger junction near the town center.
Southern wetland shorelines show new cleared areas and trails, indicating recreational park development.
